{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T02:40:54.423114+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland", "tool": "Write", "input": {"file_path": "/Users/toby/.claude/projects/-Users-toby/memory/session-2026-05-01-mioserver-fix-codesisland-connect.md", "content": "# Session 2026-05-01 \u2014 MioServer Fix + CodeIsland Connection\n\n## MioServer Fixes Applied\n\n### 1. P2003 FK Constraint Fix\n**Problem**: `POST /v1/sessions` returned P2003 because `bumpLastSeenAt()` was fire-and-forget async, causing race condition with session creation.\n\n**Fix in middleware.ts**:\n```typescript\nexport async function bumpLastSeenAt(deviceId: string): Promise<void> {\n    // ...\n    await db.device.upsert({\n        where: { id: deviceId },\n        create: { id: deviceId, name: 'JWT Device', publicKey: deviceId, lastSeenAt: new Date() },\n        update: { lastSeenAt: new Date() },\n    }).catch(() => { lastSeenWriteAt.delete(deviceId); });\n}\n```\nKey: `async` keyword + `await` in middleware call.\n\n### 2. Railway Deploy \u2014 Switch to GitHub Fork\n**Problem**: `RAILWAY_DOCKER_IMAGE` variable is IGNORED by Railway for existing services.\n**Solution**: Changed Railway source repo to `123qwe55aa/MioServer` fork, pushed all fixes there, Railway auto-deploys from fork.\n\n### 3. Legacy MioServer/ Subdirectory Removed\nDead code (git submodule) not used by Dockerfile \u2014 committed deletion to fork.\n\n### 4. Debug Endpoint Added\n```typescript\napp.get('/v1/debug/device/:deviceId', {\n    preHandler: authMiddleware,\n}, async (request) => {\n    const { deviceId } = request.params as { deviceId: string };\n    const device = await db.device.findUnique({ where: { id: deviceId } });\n    return { deviceId, exists: !!device, device };\n});\n```\n\n## CodeIsland \u2192 MioServer Connection\n\n### How it works:\n1. CodeIsland stores server URL in `UserDefaults` key `codelight-server-url`\n2. Set via: `defaults write com.codeisland.app codelight-server-url -string \"https://mio-server-production.up.railway.app\"`\n3. CodeIsland starts, reads URL, uses Ed25519 KeyManager to authenticate\n4. Auth flow: `POST /v1/auth` \u2192 verify signature \u2192 return JWT \u2192 Socket.io `/v1/updates`\n\n### CodeIsland Auth (authRoutes.ts):\n```typescript\nif (!verifySignature(challenge, signature, publicKey)) return 401;\nconst device = await db.device.upsert({ where: { publicKey }, create: { publicKey, ... } });\nconst token = createToken(device.id, config.masterSecret, ttl);\nreturn { success: true, token, deviceId: device.id };\n```\n\n### Socket.io path: `/v1/updates`\n- CodeIsland uses `connectParams` with token, Swift SocketIO library supports both auth object and query params\n- Server extracts: `socket.handshake.auth.token || socket.handshake.query.token`\n\n### Subscription: auto-trial enabled\n`enforceSubscription` defaults to true; new devices without subscription auto-start trial.\n\n## Commits Pushed to Fork\n```\n45f2f1b refactor: remove legacy MioServer/ subdirectory\na8ee4e7 fix: await device upsert before session creation + debug endpoint\n5801b65 fix: ensure device record exists before creating session (FK constraint)\n```\n\n## Key Decision\n- Railway `RAILWAY_DOCKER_IMAGE` variable is **completely ineffective** for existing services \u2014 Railway ignores it\n- Only two options work: (1) fork + change source repo, or (2) Railway source upload\n"}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
