{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T03:37:52.591750+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland", "tool": "Bash", "input": {"command": "# Check what deviceIds are on the server - look for any with kind='mac' or name containing 'Mac'\n# We can check via the auth - but we don't know Mac's deviceId yet\n# Let's check pairing links with the Mac's shortCode via the pairing endpoint\n\n# First, let's see if there are any devices with shortCode set (Macs registered)\ncurl -s \"https://mio-server-production.up.railway.app/v1/sessions\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiAiSFMyNTYiLCAidHlwIjogIkpXVCJ9.eyJkZXZpY2VJZCI6ICJiZGQwNmI0OTBmMmQ0Yzk2ODQyYzQ5OGM1ZDMyMTM0OSIsICJleHAiOiAxNzc3NjkxOTQ3LCAiaWF0IjogMTc3NzYwNTU0N30.H23f9wmvrQMUDsp5w3NeS5SLqxtjwKzu0RGMWz_S-Oc\" | \\\n  python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); [print(s['ownerDeviceId'], s['ownerDeviceName'], s['ownerDeviceKind']) for s in d['sessions']]\" 2>/dev/null | sort -u", "description": "Check unique devices owning sessions"}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-01T03:47:15.983228+00:00", "session_id": "71f1d2d8-1358-4b95-a8a7-f26fc0827908", "cwd": "/Users/toby/Documents/Projects/CodeIsland", "tool": "Edit", "input": {"file_path": "/Users/toby/.claude/projects/-Users-toby/memory/session-2026-05-01-mioserver-fix-codesisland-connect.md", "old_string": "## Key Decision\n- Railway `RAILWAY_DOCKER_IMAGE` variable is **completely ineffective** for existing services \u2014 Railway ignores it\n- Only two options work: (1) fork + change source repo, or (2) Railway source upload", "new_string": "## Key Decision\n- Railway `RAILWAY_DOCKER_IMAGE` variable is **completely ineffective** for existing services \u2014 Railway ignores it\n- Only two options work: (1) fork + change source repo, or (2) Railway source upload\n\n## Critical Issue: Device Isolation\n\n**Problem**: Each device (sync-daemon, CodeIsland Mac, iPhone) has a unique deviceId based on their auth method:\n- sync-daemon: JWT with HMAC-SHA256, deviceId = random UUID hex\n- CodeIsland Mac: Ed25519 keypair, deviceId = hash of public key (from server response)\n- iPhone CodeLight: Ed25519 keypair, deviceId = hash of public key\n\n`GET /v1/sessions` uses `getAccessibleDeviceIds()` which returns only own deviceId + linked DeviceLinks.\n**Result**: iPhone can only see sessions from paired Macs, not from sync-daemon.\n\n**sync-daemon sessions exist** on server:\n```json\n{\"id\":\"cmomadc3y...\",\"deviceId\":\"bdd06b490f2d4c96842c498c5d321349\",\"ownerDeviceKind\":\"ios\"}\n```\nBut this deviceId belongs to sync-daemon, NOT to Mac CodeIsland.\n\n**Architecture reality**:\n- Mac has NO Claude Code running \u2192 MessageRelay never creates sessions on server\n- sync-daemon on Mac syncs Claude Code sessions from JSONL \u2192 creates sessions under sync-daemon's deviceId\n- CodeIsland Mac has different deviceId from sync-daemon\n- **They need to share deviceId OR sync-daemon needs to act on behalf of Mac's deviceId**\n\n**User's CodeIsland** is upstream MioMioOS/MioIsland (not CodeIsland fork), uses upstream repo.\nServer URL configured: `https://mio-server-production.up.railway.app` \u2705\nMac shows \"online\" in CodeLight tab \u2705\nPairing \"succeeds\" but no sessions appear because Mac has no Claude Code sessions.\n\n**Solution options**:\n1. Make Mac's CodeIsland and sync-daemon share the same deviceId (hard \u2014 different auth methods)\n2. Remove deviceId filter from GET /v1/sessions (quick hack for testing)\n3. Have Mac run Claude Code so MessageRelay creates sessions under Mac's deviceId\n4. sync-daemon should create sessions using Mac's CodeIsland deviceId (not its own)", "replace_all": false}, "result": "PreToolUse"}
